properties.name: Albania
properties.info: The Eagle and specifically the Golden Eagle, which is a resident raptor in the Albanian highlands, is the national symbol of Albania. In Albanian language, the country of Albania is called Shqipëri (Land of Eagles) and its people are called Shqiptarë (Sons of Eagles).

properties.name: Armenia
properties.info: Eagle is the national animal of the Armenian state. Due to its unique features designed to fly at high altitudes, there is no chance to mix the national animal of Armenia with other birds. The reason why Eagle is so important is because of its courage, wisdom, power, nobility and patience.

properties.name: Austria
properties.info: The Black Eagle is the national animal of Austria. It is a bird of prey.  The Eagle articulated on Austria’s national coat of arms and is usually the country’s official bird and also animal sign. Boldness, power, and victory are some of the features which make it national symbol worthy.

properties.name: Azerbaijan
properties.info: Azerbaijan’s national animal, Karabakh horse is one of the fastest horses in the world. The Karabakh horse is a type of horse which is renowned for speed and fortitude. It is characteristically hardy, physically powerful, tough and sure-footed. The horse is often used in the traditional Karabakh horse riding game Chovqan.

properties.name: Belarus
properties.info: The European bison, commonly called the wisent, is seen as a symbol of Belarus and the Belavezha Forest. It is also featured on the symbols of Brest Oblast. European bison is one of the most endangered mammal species in the world. The European bison is very important for the sustainable endurance of European biodiversity, especially when it comes to plants.

properties.name: Belgium
properties.info: The lion, especially the Leo Belgicus (Latin for Belgian Lion) has been used as a heraldic animal to represent the Benelux for centuries. A heraldic lion can be seen on the Belgian coat of arms and can be seen as the countries de facto national animal.

properties.name: Bosnia and Herzegovina
properties.info: The Tornjak is the national animal of Bosnia and Herzegovina. It is a large, well-proportioned and agile livestock guardian dog. Its long and thick hair is adequate to protect it against the cold weather during winter. The clear, self-confident and calm look it possesses makes it a good choice for Bosnia and Herzegovina’s national animal.

properties.name: Bulgaria
properties.info: The lion is the national symbol of Bulgaria depicted on the country’s coat of arms. Bulgaria’s currency is the lev, the name originally deriving from the Bulgarian word “luv” meaning “lion” in English. Lion is an emblem of Bulgaria’s stateliness and hence a part of the nation’s official culture, its image appearing mostly in representations of kings and millitary commanders.

properties.name: Croatia
properties.info: Marten is the national animal of Croatia. It has small-headed mustelid, long tail and soft, thick brown hair with a yellow or white spot on the throat, feeds on birds, eggs, and rodents; lives in the forests of Europe and is highly prized for its skin. The marten is the common motif on the Croatian kuna coins.

properties.name: Cyprus
properties.info: The Cypriot Mouflon is the national animal of Cyprus. It is also known as Cyprus Mountain Goat or Agrino. The national animal of Cyprus is a type of wild sheep which is unique in the whole world and the largest mammal in Cyprus. They roam free in the extensive forests of western Troodos.

properties.name: Czech Republic
properties.info: The lion, or more specifically the mythical double-tailed lion is the national animal of the Czech Republic. It’s meant to represent power and sovereignty. It is represented on the coat of arms and is seen wearing a crown with its double tails crossed. Double-tailed or not, the lion is a national symbol of many countries of the world.

properties.name: Denmark
properties.info: The Danish national animal is the mute swan, which is famously known for its snow-white feathers, and for being the main character in H. C. Andersen’s fairy tale, The Ugly Duckling. The swan is considered as a symbol of beauty, peace and the power of the country.

properties.name: Estonia
properties.info: Estonia's national animal is the wolf. It was a symbol of wild and untouched nature. Estonian bogs and forest massifs are sometimes also pointedly called ‘wolf lands’. There is probably no other animal in that region that has influenced the local language and culture as much as the wolf.

properties.name: Finland
properties.info: The chestnut bear, also known as the brown bear is the national animal of Finland. It is large in size, only being rivaled by the polar bear. Their most distinctive feature is the shoulder hump. This hump contains energy which helps the bear dig up roots in search of food.

properties.name: France
properties.info: One of the national emblems of France, the Coq Gaulois (the Gallic Rooster) decorated French flags during the Revolution. It is the symbol of the French people because of the play on words of the Latin gallus meaning Gaul and gallus meaning coq, or rooster. It was used to symbolize vigilance.

properties.name: Georgia
properties.info: The white-tailed deer is the official state mammal of Georgia. It is easily recognized by most Georgians, found throughout the state (there are about 1 million deer in Georgia) and sports a tremendous economic impact through hunting.

properties.name: Germany
properties.info: The black Eagle is the national animal of Germany. The black eagle belongs to the class of aves and the scientific name of Germans eagle is Hieraatus Spilogaster. Eagle is the symbol of courage, strength, and victory. Eagle is the most popular Bird in Germany. The ancient people loved eagles very much and they reflected that in their art.

properties.name: Greece
properties.info: Dolphin is Greece's national animal. Etymologically speaking, the word ‘dolphin’ comes from the ancient Greek delphis, itself related to the Greek delphus, or womb, so the animal’s name more or less means ‘a ‘fish’ with a womb.’ As such, the dolphin’s role in human culture can be traced back to ancient times, where they appear in many myths.

properties.name: Hungary
properties.info: Hungary's national animal is a falcon, or more specifically a mythological representation of a falcon or a hawk called the Turul. It's a bird of prey and widely represented in Hungarian tradition and a national symbol of modern Hungary and Transylvania.

properties.name: Iceland
properties.info: The national Animal of Iceland is Gyrfalcon. It’s the largest species of falcon. It is a bird of prey found in the coastal area and on the island.

properties.name: Ireland
properties.info: Despite not officialy having a national animal, the Irish Hare (Lepus timidus) has been described as a national animal of Ireland. It is one of Ireland’s longest established indigenous species of mammals.

properties.name: Italy
properties.info: The wolf is considered the unofficial symbol of the Italy by the most because of the wolf's place in Italy's history and folklore. The grey wolf, also known as the Apennine Wolf, lives in the Apennine Italian Mountains, Switzerland and part of France

properties.name: Kazakhstan
properties.info: The national animal of Kazakhstan is the golden eagle. It represents the country's strength, independence, freedom and flight into the future. For centuries, this eagle was incorporated into the flags of Kazakh tribes. It is now one of the main pictures on the current Kazakh flag, adopted in 1992.

properties.name: Kosovo
properties.info: Although the population of it is quite small, the Balkan Lynx could be considered one of the national animals of Kosovo. The Balkan lynx is considered a critically endangered species by the International Union for Conservation of Nature (IUCN) and is the highest risk category for endangered species.

properties.name: Latvia
properties.info: The white wagtail(a very cute birb) is considered to be Latvia's national bird. It is frequently mentioned in Latvian folk songs as a symbol of hard work and diligence. It was affirmed as the national bird in May of 1960 by the International Council for Bird Preservation while they were meeting in Tokyo.

properties.name: Lithuania
properties.info: The white stork is the national animal of Lithuania. It was declared as the national animal of Lithuania in the year 1973. Citizens of Lithuania believe the white stork brings harmony to families on whose land they nest. This has made it to be celebrated across the country. They also believe that storks can bring babies when they nest on an individual’s land that is infertile.

properties.name: Luxembourg
properties.info: Lion is the national animal of Luxembourg. Scientifically they are called panther Leo. The color of Luxembourg lion is brown and males dominate in size over females. About 34000 lions are present in country but nowadays the population is in danger and threatened because humans have disturbed their natural habitat.

properties.name: Moldova
properties.info: Sheep represent one of the most common animals for the country of Moldova. There are approximately 1.3 million sheep and goats in the Republic of Moldova. The numbers of sheep and goats, as well as other livestock, does not seem to have declined with the transition to a new economy.

properties.name: Montenegro
properties.info: The animal which could represent Montenegro is a lion. The lion passant on the inescutcheon on their coat of arms is as a sign of episcopal authority and could have been conceived of as a metaphor for the Lion of Judah. It represents Montenegro's Christian struggle to stay independent and devoted to their own path in history.

properties.name: Netherlands
properties.info: Te black-tailed godwit was voted the Netherlands’ national bird. In summer, they have bright orangey-brown chests and bellies, but in winter they're more greyish-brown. Their most distinctive features are their long beaks and legs, and the black and white stripes on their wings.

properties.name: North Macedonia
properties.info: Considered to be a national symbol, and placed on the back of the 5 denar coin, the Macedonian wildcat, the Balkan lynx, is one of the rarest animals in the world. Around 100 specimens are believed to be scattered around the Balkans, most of which inhabit the National Park Mavrovo.

properties.name: Norway
properties.info: Norway's most recognizable animal is the fjord horse. It is Norway's oldest horse breed. Fjord horse is distinguished by its unequaled dependability. For centuries Norwegian breeders have been determined to improve the breed while emphasizing the calm and gentle temperament. They are easily broken and need no retraining, even after spending months at pasture untouched.

properties.name: Poland
properties.info: The national animal of Poland is the European bison. In Poland, three quarters of the local population of these great mammals live in the wild. You can come across them not only in Bialowieza Forest, but also in the Bieszczady Mountains, in Masuria and in West Pomerania.

properties.name: Portugal
properties.info: Iberian wolf is the national animal of Portugal. The Iberian wolf is a subspecies of grey wolf and is native to Iberian Peninsula, Spain and Portugal. Iberian wolfs are human friendly in various circumstances. Due to this they have been seen in the villages and towns of Portugal, where they search for the food devoid of any fear.

properties.name: Romania
properties.info: The Eurasian lynx is the national animal of Romania. It is a medium-sized cat, which is commonly native to Siberia, Central, Eastern, and Southern Asia, Northern, Central and Eastern Europe. The Eurasian lynx is a solitary animal; a secretive creature that prefers dense forests full of hiding places and stalking opportunities.

properties.name: Russia
properties.info: Russia's most significant animal is the bear. The bear symbolizes strength, endurance and resilience. Though not officially being Russia's national animal and sometimes representing bad traits such as arrogance and laziness, the bear has been a part of this country's history for a long time.

properties.name: Serbia
properties.info: Serbia is home to a wide range of animals, but none resonate quite as strongly within the national consciousness as the proud, brave gray wolf: a hugely important part of Serbian mythology and a recurring character in the nation’s epic poetry. There is a stable population of around 500 gray wolves in Serbia.

properties.name: Slovakia
properties.info: Though there are no official or unofficial national animals of Slovakia, a bear is a widely recognized animal around the country and also mentioned in some of their poems.

properties.name: Slovenia
properties.info: One of the most peculiar animals which can be seen in Slovenia is olm. It is a species of blind amphibians endemic to the the deep underground caves of the Dinaric karst of southeastern Europe. These creatures can be best observed in Postojnska Jama cave complex in Slovenia, a well developed tourist spot with a museum which displays a captive colony of olm.

properties.name: Spain
properties.info: The national animal of Spain is the bull. The bull is also an important component of Spanish culture in general. For instance, Spain participates in bullfighting and the traditional Running of the Bulls. In recent years, some of these activities have brought some controversy to the country’s traditions.

properties.name: Sweden
properties.info: Moose is the official National animal of Sweden. Because of Sweden’s environment and low temperatures, moose are commonly found in Forests, mostly in northern areas. The scientific name for Moose is Alces Alces. They are also called Elk by locals.

properties.name: Switzerland
properties.info: Switzerland currently does not have a national animal, but the animal most commonly associated with Switzerland, or Alpine culture in general, is the cow. Living up high among the Swiss Alps, many cow farmers keep their family traditions alive, earning a living by making cheese.

properties.name: Turkey
properties.info: The official national animal of Turkey is the Gray Wolf. Its scientific name is Canis lupus. Grey wolves fit the Turks very well. They are heavy meat eaters like the first nomadic Turk tribes. They are weak in comparison to many other predators. However, they always hunt with a group with every group having an alpha male who is the leader. The idea fits Turkish people well.

properties.name: Ukraine
properties.info: One of the most significant birds in Ukraine is the common nightingale. In Ukrainian folklore nightingale is a symbol of volition, high inspiration and unsurpassed talent. This bird is often mentioned in Ukrainian songs and poems as a harbinger of spring.

properties.name: United Kingdom
properties.info: Though not an official symbol, British Bulldog is a dog species widely spread in United Kingdom. Bulldogs originally were used to drive cattle to market and to compete in a bloody sport called bullbaiting. Today, they’re gentle companions who love kids.
